      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, the term \"fake news\" has rapidly evolved into a potent political weapon rather than purely a description of falsehoods. Opponents often deploy the label as a rhetorical tactic to delegitimize credible journalism or dissenting voices. This usage muddies the waters, allowing legitimate news reporting to be dismissed unfairly as mere propaganda. Consequently, the term itself often functions as a shield against scrutiny rather than an objective measure of truth.",
      "source": "target",
